Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), desktop-file-utils, dh-apparmor, gettext, gir1.2-glib-2.0-dev <!nogir>, gobject-introspection (>= 1.80) <!nogir>, intltool, libadwaita-1-dev, libarchive-dev, libcairo2-dev, libfontconfig-dev, libfreetype-dev, libgee-0.8-dev, libglib2.0-dev (>= 2.44), libgtk-4-dev (>= 4.12), libgucharmap-2-90-dev, libjson-glib-dev, libnautilus-extension-dev, libnemo-extension-dev, libpango1.0-dev (>= 1.45), libsoup-3.0-dev, libsqlite3-dev, libthunarx-3-dev, libwebkitgtk-6.0-dev, libxml2-dev, meson (>= 0.53~), python3, valac (>= 0.42~), yelp-tools
Description: font management application for the GNOME desktop Font Manager is intended to provide a way for average users to easily manage desktop fonts, without having to resort to command line tools or editing configuration files by hand. While designed primarily with the GNOME Desktop Environment in mind, it should work well with other Gtk+ desktop environments.
